      "writtenOn": "2020-10-09T01:06:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "You probably ran into that problem where the TypeScript compiler thinks you want the Node.JS version of setTimeout() instead of the browser\u0027s.\n\nA workaround we\u0027ve used before is to call window.setTimeout() instead, which returns a number. Then this line can be rewritten as:\n\n  private _timeout: number \u003d 0;\n\nNote that there\u0027s no need for (number | null) because windows.setTimeout() always returns a positive number, so the number 0 can be used to represent the absence of a timeout.\n\nReference: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/WindowOrWorkerGlobalScope/setTimeout",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 48,
        "startChar": 20,
        "endLine": 48,
        "endChar": 50
