      "message": "Please define a type for the \"detail\" of any custom events, e.g.\n\n  export type Mode \u003d \u0027play\u0027 | \u0027pause\u0027;\n\n  // Naming convention: \u003cComponentName\u003e\u003cEventName\u003eEventDetail\n  export interface PlaySkModeChangedManuallyEventDetail {\n    readonly mode: Mode;\n  }\n\nThen the event can be dispatched as follows:\n\n  this.dispatchEvent(\n    new CustomEvent\u003cPlaySkModeChangedManuallyEventDetail\u003e(\n      \u0027mode-changed-manually\u0027, {\n        detail: {mode: this._mode}, // The compiler will type check this.\n        bubbles: true\n      }));\n\nAdvantages:\n- The compiler will produce an error if the event is accidentally dispatched with details of the wrong type.\n- Client code can use the event detail type and avoid error-prone type assertions.\n- More self documenting.\n\nFor an example, please see https://github.com/google/elements-sk/blob/ba8f06c9433de113518b7c348d1f31b2e4d9c953/src/errorMessage.ts#L39.",
